item.title: NAB slashes H1 payout, to raise $3.5bn
item.description: National Australia Bank has slashed its interim dividend to 30 cents and launched a $3.5 billion capital raising after its first-half cash earnings more than halved to $1.46 billion.

item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
Calls for climate focus after coronavirus
item.description: Governments are being warned not to redirect resources earmarked for climate change in recovery efforts after coronavirus.

item.title: Woman drives onto Vic station overpass
item.description: A woman is expected to be charged with drink-driving after allegedly driving her car onto the pedestrian overpass at a Melbourne train station.

item.title: Victoria’s fire danger period comes to end
item.description: Victoria's fire danger season has officially come to a close after a devastating summer in which five people died and 1.5 million hectares of land was destroyed.

item.title: Palaszczuk open to Queensland NRL return
item.description: Queensland Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk is open to top-level rugby league returning to the state if the NRL can show it will provide a safe workplace for players and the community.

item.title: One million Aussies download COVIDSafe app
item.description: More than one million Australians have downloaded the coronavirus tracing app within hours of its release.

item.title: Plan to reopen Italy after strict lockdown
item.description: Italy is set to ease a number of coronavirus-related restrictions from May 4, permitting more outdoor sports and exercise, Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte says.

item.title: US praises Aust warship in South China Sea
item.description: The US Navy has heaped praise on the Royal Australian Navy for taking part in South China Sea exercises that show allies in the region both nations have the "same interest in ensuring freedom of navigation".

item.title: More US states to reopen amid job shortage
item.description: Another wave of US states are poised to lift coronavirus restrictions this week against the warnings of many public health experts.
